						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 90 sheep and another of 50 for burning a perpetual lamp and a day lamp in the temple of Tirukkaṟkuḍi-Paramēśvara at <hi rend="bold">Nandivarmamaṅgalam</hi> by Pērānan Viranārāyaṇaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śembiyaṉ-Mārāyaṉ a <hi rend="italic">perundanam</hi> (officer) under <hi rend="bold">Vīraśōḻa-Iḷaṅgōvēḷār of Koḍumbāḷūr.</hi> Kaṟkuḍi is the ancient name of Uyyakkoṇḍāṉ-Tirumalai and finds mention in the <hi rend="italic">Dēvāram.</hi> This has been assigned to <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
